<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Floats, shifting down below all other floated elements</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visuren.html#floats" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Left floated boxes shift down until it fits." />
        <style type="text/css">
            #div1
            {
                background: orange;
                height: 1in;
                width: 1.25in;
            }
            #div2
            {
                background: purple;
                height: 0.25in;
                margin-top: 0.5in;
                width: 0.75in;
            }
            #div3
            {
                background: yellow;
                width: 0.5in;
                height: 0.25in;
            }
            #div4
            {
                background-color: blue;
                height: 1in;
                float: left;
                width: 1in;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the blue box is below all other boxes.</p>
        <div>
           <div id="div1"></div>
           <div id="div2"></div>
           <div id="div3"></div>
           <div id="div4"></div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>